<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-390-832  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 390 832.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 26 1989 n544 pT4(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DA in the '90s: breadth and depth. (design automation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Costa, Frank; Wolfson, Marv.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>From its inception nearly 10 years ago, Computer-Aided Engineering(CAD) has evolved rapidly toward a goal of comprehensive systemsdesign within a single, standardized environment.andP;  The designautomation system of the 1990s will accelerate this movementtoward an integrated operating environment capable of concurrentfunctioning.andP;  This can be traced from the early period of designautomation, when frameworks were limited and little interactiontook place among various disciplines, through the growth of dataexchange and frameworks to the present day.andP;  The growth andintegration of frameworks, disciplines and methodologies willcharacterize the evolution of automated design, as systems aredeveloped that make it possible for designers to analyze theinteraction of hardware, software and mechanical elements of asystem.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer-Aided DesignComputer-Aided EngineeringAutomationIntegrated SystemsStandardizationSoftware Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>